-- Greece Plans Tax Cuts for Business, Individuals, To Vima Says
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-01-16T09:48:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/greece-plans-tax-cuts-for-business-individuals-to-vima-says.html
Greece  may reduce the tax burden on
private individuals and businesses as part of plans for a new
national tax system, To Vima  said , without citing anyone.  Particular attention will be paid to lowering tax on
industries that have seen a marked slowdown in economic activity
such as real estate, the Athens-based news paper  said.  The new tax legislation will be simplified and adopt
international practices for combating  tax evasion , To Vima said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  